                  <handDesc><!--ACHTUNG! first HandNote comes from writing system in Ethiospare. the others are one for each CHANGE OF HAND-->
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine, regular and careful</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red.</seg>
                        <date>Second half of the 19th century.</date>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra (at times only partly rubricated, s. fols. 3va, 4ra); incipit and heading of the text; on the incipit page, a few words are rubricated alternating with words in black; names of the feasts (fol. 8r, 11r, 62v, 64v, 71r, 73v, 87r); indications for daily readings (fols. 41v,); the word mǝʾǝraf followed by the number of the chapter, the first and the third lines of the chapter; elements of the punctuation signs and numerals, numbers of quires, lines separating passages.</seg>
                     </handNote>
