                           <desc>: Note concerning events in the lives (?) of Evangelists (Matthew, Mark, Luke and John).</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note>
                           Hardly readable.
                        </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a2">
                           <locus target="#98rb">ff. 98rb-99</locus>
                           <desc>ra: Text concerning the value of common Orthodox prayers.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note>
                           In Amharic.
                        </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a3">
                           <locus target="#99ra">f. 99ra</locus>
                           <desc>: Note concerning dates of celebrating some feasts, with a small, crude calendaric table.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note>
                           Written in Gǝʿǝz and Amharic.
                        </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a4">
                           <locus target="#99va">f. 99va</locus>
                           <desc>: Unidentified text.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note>
                           In Amharic. Recent and hardly readable, written in pink.
                        </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a5">
                           <locus target="#99vb">f. 99vb</locus>
                           <desc>: ʾAsmat-prayer. </desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note>
                           The title (?)  is written in the upper margin: “And you who have terrified the idols...”.
                        </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="a6">
                           <locus target="#100v">f. 100v</locus>
                           <desc>: Protective prayer to God, a recipe for a certain medicine, and a short protective prayer mentioning St Mary.</desc>
                           <quote xml:lang="gez"/>
                           <quote xml:lang="en"/>
                           <note>
                           Written in Gǝʿǝz and Amharic.
                        </note>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- A chain of black dots and a red line, probably separating the text passages (?), on fols.: 21v, 23r, 41r, 41v, 42v, 49r, 50r, 53r, 61v, 62v, 63r, 64v, 67r, 71r, 72r, 73r, 77v, 87r, 93v.&#xD;
- Crude drawing of a cross with an inscription above: zǝ-Masqal za-ʾAbba, <locus target="1r">1r</locus>.&#xD;
- Numerous corrections of the text (written interlineally and in the margins) by another hand: <locus target="3va">3va</locus>, 4rab, 4vab, 5rab, 6rab, 9va, 10rab, 10vb, 51va, 73vb, 84vb. &#xD;
- Text erasures: <locus target="29ra">29ra</locus>b. &#xD;
- Crudely written notes in pen: <locus target="6r">6r</locus>, 17v, 75v, 100rv.</item>
